<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="promoter">Promoter</a> - A region of <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a> that drives the <a href="#expression">expression</a> of a <a href="#gene">gene</a> following it on a piece of <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a>. Most <a href="#promoter">promoters</a> are directional, meaning they drive the expression of a <a href="#gene">gene</a> only on one side (<a href="#3_prime_end_3">3'</a>) of it. Some <a href="#promoter">promoters</a> are bidirectionally driven and will drive the expression on both the <a href="#5_prime_end_5">5'</a> and <a href="#3_prime_end_3">3'</a> side.